# tRPC Data Fetching

tRPC provides two different ways to call your API, depending on whether you're in a **Server Component** or **Client Component**. Using the wrong one will cause runtime errors.

## Rule: Use the Correct Import for Your Context

| Context | Import From | How It Works |
|---------|-------------|--------------|
| Server Component / Server Action / API Route | `@/trpc/server` | Direct function call, no HTTP, no React hooks |
| Client Component | `@/trpc/react` | React hooks, calls go over HTTP to `/api/trpc` |

## Server Components — `serverCaller`

Use when you're in a Server Component, Server Action, or API route. This performs a **direct function call** — no HTTP request, no network latency.

```tsx
// src/app/courses/page.tsx (Server Component — no "use client")
import { serverCaller } from "@/trpc/server";

export default async function CoursesPage() {
  const courses = await serverCaller.course.list();
  return <CourseList initialData={courses} />;
}
```

```ts
// In a Server Action
import { serverCaller } from "@/trpc/server";

export async function createCourse(formData: FormData) {
  "use server";
  await serverCaller.course.create({ name: formData.get("name") as string });
}
```

## Client Components — `api` (React Hooks)

Use when you're in a Client Component (has `"use client"`). This uses React Query hooks and makes HTTP requests.

```tsx
"use client";

import { api } from "@/trpc/react";

export function CourseList() {
  const { data, isLoading, error } = api.course.list.useQuery();

  if (isLoading) return <div>Loading...</div>;
  if (error) return <div>Error: {error.message}</div>;
  return <ul>{data?.map((c) => <li key={c.id}>{c.name}</li>)}</ul>;
}
```

**Mutations:**
```tsx
const utils = api.useUtils();
const createCourse = api.course.create.useMutation({
  onSuccess: () => utils.course.list.invalidate(),
});
```

## ⚠️ Do NOT Mix

| ❌ Wrong | Why |
|----------|-----|
| `serverCaller` in a Client Component | `serverCaller` runs on server; Client Components run in browser |
| `api` in a Server Component | Hooks only work in Client Components |
